40|$|This {{invention}} {{proposes a}} component distribution scheme, and a mechanism that automatically loads and installs components from a client machine to an Embedded Server. NOVELTY - The method involves transmitting a component loader (12) from the embedded server (1) to an application server (2), then the component loader transmits the business application (13) from a component server to the applications server. The component loader {{is sent to}} the application server using a network address stored in the embedded server. USE - For establishing a communications connection between embedded server and <b>client</b> computer. <b>ADVANTAGE</b> - Overcomes certain disadvantages of conventional arrangements, e. g. the high costs of configuration. DETAILED DESCRIPTION - INDEPENDENT CLAIMS are also included for the following: a computer program for establishing a communications connection between embedded server and client computer. DESCRIPTION OF DRAWING(S) - The drawing shows a schematic representation of a structure of data processing units for establishing a communications connection between embedded server and client compute...|$|R
40|$|The paper {{analyzes}} {{the effects of}} informational asymmetries on the market structure of the banking industry in a multi-period model of spatial competition. All lenders face uncertainty with regard to borrowers’ creditworthiness, but, {{in the process of}} lending, incumbent banks gather proprietary information about their <b>clients,</b> acquiring an <b>advantage</b> over potential entrants. These informational asymmetries are an important determinant of the industry structure and may represent a barrier to entry for new banks. The paper shows that, in contrast with traditional models of horizontal differentiation, the steady-state equilibrium is characterized by a finite number of banks {{even in the absence of}} fixed costs. ...|$|R
